issue.title: The Host Switch system cause a lot of issues in multiplayer
issue.body:
### Describe the bug

The host switch system causes numerous issues and is quite unstable. Most of the time, it results in minor lag that's not too disruptive, but roughly one out of ten times, all players suddenly enter the falling animation and start sliding across the ground.

For context, I'm using the physic-based Controller along with the built-in Network Helper.

Occasionally — though more rarely — the entire lobby becomes unstable: some players completely lose gravity, others end up stuck inside another player’s body, and various other strange behaviors can occur.

### To Reproduce

.

### Expected behavior

The host switch should be smooth and almost unnoticeable and shouldn't break entire lobby.

### Media/Files

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/eade22e9-1f34-49d0-a1dd-965b76a9d62c) 

Here you can see the falling animation issue after an host switch, it stay like that until you wait a long time or relog.



### Additional context

I use :

 The physic-based facepunch controller 

The Network Helper to manage player spawn

Network settings : Quick Play Launch Mode 

Game : Resource Haven
